# Vibework

This is a **vibe prototype starter**: go from Figma (or a sketch) to a clickable, deployable UI fast. Optimize for iteration speed, not production architecture.

## Defaults

- Prefer the smallest change that makes the screen work
- Build in `src/app/pages/`; keep interactive bits in small `"use client"` islands
- Discover UI with Astryx (`vp run astryx -- …`) — do not invent a parallel design system
- Use `vp` for install, dev, build, check, and tests (see Vite+ rule)
- Full stack notes live in `AGENTS.md` — follow it when conventions conflict with generic advice

## Figma → code

When the user shares a Figma URL or design:

1. Use the Figma MCP (`get_design_context`, `get_screenshot`, `get_metadata`) — do not guess layout from memory
2. Load the project skill `figma-to-prototype` and follow it
3. Map frames to Astryx components + Tailwind layout, not pixel-perfect custom CSS

If Figma tools are missing, tell the user to install the Figma Cursor plugin (`/add-plugin figma`) or enable the project MCP server.
